The paper deals with the synthesis of systems from their behavioural specifications, which is a topic in formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The focus is on register transducers, which are systems that store data-input into registers and later output the content of a register, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also mentions the use of temporal logic for specifications, which falls under logic in computer science (cs.LT). Finally, the paper discusses scalability issues, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
